item.description:
The County Sheriff is the highest elected official in the county. They are the Chief Law Enforcement Officer. They are empowered and charged with protecting the Citizens of the county, their property and their Rights. Frank will be discussing the history of, and potential for restoring freedom through, the Office of the County Sheriff. One of our members, Frank Szabo, has decided to throw his hat into the ring and run against incumbent James Hardy for Hillsborough County.

Bio: Frank Szabo has been fighting locally for Freedom for many years, having legally challenged zoning and the Income Tax being applied to private Citizens. Frank was the Pa. State Coordinator for We The People Congress, County Coordinator for The Sheriff Project and a Pa. State Coordinator for Ron Paul's 2008 Presidential Campaign.
